This paper deals with natural language processing (NLP) and specifically focuses on detecting sarcasm and irony, which falls under the category of computational linguistics (cs.CL). The use of deep learning techniques and character-level vector representations also suggests that it could fall under the categories of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). Additionally, the paper deals with the challenge of capturing context-dependent features, which could also place it under the category of cognitive computing (cs.CC) or social and information networks (cs.SI).
